<section class="block-section story">
  <span class="section-tag">📖 Story</span>
  <h2>Why this block matters</h2>
  <p class="sub">A neighbourhood has to deliver several things at once, and they pull against each other.</p>
  <p>A liveable neighbourhood has to deliver several things at the same time: access to daily needs, housing, green and blue space, heat comfort, and flood resilience. These are the city-scale version of ecosystem services, the things a place provides for the people and ecology that depend on it. In Chennai these systems are under real stress, and they interact: paving for density removes the permeable land that buffers floods, while green and blue space cools the heat but competes for the same area as housing.</p>
